McCauley (Mike) Whiting, Jr






FOR IMMEDIATE
            RELEASE
April 22, 2003
 
News Release
 
Northwood University to Award Macauley Whiting,
              Jr. with Honorary Doctorate Degree
 
West Palm Beach, Fla. ---
          At its 2003 commencement ceremony, Northwood University will award
          an honorary doctorate degree to Macauley (Mike) Whiting, co-founder
          of Decker Energy International, Inc., for his entrepreneurial leadership.
          The commencement will be held on May 21 at the Raymond F. Kravis Center
          for the Performing Arts, 701 Okeechobee Boulevard. More than 2,000
          students will graduate from all of the NU campuses this year.
 
Whiting graduated from
          Princeton University in 1978 and began a career with Dow Chemical Company
          in Freeport, Texas. In 1982 he co-founded Decker Energy International,
          Inc. of Winter Park, Florida, which develops, acquires, owns and operates
          environmentally friendly power generating facilities, especially those
          using renewable resources. His professional services include trustee
          and secretary of the Herbert H. and Grace A. Dow Foundation, Midland,
          Michigan; and trustee of Northwood University, Midland, Michigan. Dedicated
          to children, he has coached little league baseball teams for more than
          10 years, including one team that played in the Senior Little League
          World Series in 2000.
 
"It is a great day
          for our institution to honor Mike Whiting with the Doctor of Laws,
          Honoris Causa," said NU Provost John Haynie. "Mike has grown
          up with Northwood by virtue of the fact that his father, Macauley Whiting
          Sr., has been a trustee of Northwood University since its beginnings.
          Mike Whiting is an accomplished entrepreneur and businessman and
          knows, as a trustee of Northwood himself, of the uniqueness of Northwood's
          educational approach. As a result, he can connect with students and
          graduates on many levels."
 
Northwood University is
          a private, accredited college offering bachelor and associate degrees
          in a variety of business management curriculums, including accounting,
          international business, banking & finance, automotive marketing & management
          and more. Northwood spans three campuses in Midland, Michigan; Cedar
          Hill, Texas; and West Palm Beach, Florida, as well as 40 extension
          centers worldwide. The Florida campus has more than 1,000 students
          enrolled.
-30-
 


 





