Background

		Mr. Macauley Whiting, Jr., also known as Mike, served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Decker Energy International, Inc. Mr. Whiting founded Decker Energy International in 1982 and built up until 2012, when he sold the company. Previously, Mr. Whiting was a Senior Research Engineer. From 1978 to 1982, he was with Dow Chemical Co. Freeport, Texas. He has been a Director of AgroFresh Solutions, Inc. since July 31, 2015. He has served as President of the ... Herbert H. and Grace A. Dow Foundation since April 2014. Mr. Whiting served the Herbert H. and Grace A. Dow Foundation as a trustee since 1996 and was appointed Treasurer in 2005. Mr. Whiting holds a B.S.E. degree, cum laude, in Chemical Engineering from Princeton University.Read Full Background




